      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_NaturePress_Lesson_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b590a2b94e82b1ad</T>
      <T n="text">0x4C0D4BA4<!--The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Nature Press</b></font> allows Sims to bring the beauty of the outdoors inside by pressing plants and flowers to decorate candles and wall art. Sims may also add Fairy Dust when crafting objects to create enchanted versions, which carry emotional auras.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_NaturePress_Lesson_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b590a2b94e82b1ae</T>
      <T n="text">0xB154B8C9<!--The Nature Press offers a wide range of ingredients, from common to rare. Sims can easily purchase common ingredients directly from the Nature Press, while others can be discovered through Foraging or by growing harvestable plants. Ingredients include flowers, fruits, vegetables, and even insects! To explore the full list, simply select the Nature Press and browse the available crafting items.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_NaturePress_Lesson_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b590a2b94e82b1af</T>
      <T n="text">0xF887F25A<!--Sims can craft two types of items with the Nature Press: Art and Candlesâ€”both beautifully adorned with natural ingredients. By adding Fairy Dust, these creations become enchanted, providing a Happy or Flirty emotional aura for nearby Sims once placed on the lot. Select an enchanted object and choose <font color="#199C2C"><b>Enable Emotional Aura</b></font> to activate the effect.\n\nCrafted items appear in the Sim's inventory, ready to showcase their wild creations at home.--></T>
    </U>
